I wrote a very simple serial port driver, when I write data to the serial port, after more than 200 ms delay, NSH crash will occur!!!

```
#include <fcntl.h>
#include <stdio.h>

extern "C" __EXPORT int serial_buggy_code_main(int argc, char *argv[]);

int serial_buggy_code_main(int argc, char *argv[]) {
uint8_t buffer[16];
int fd_ = ::open("/dev/ttyS1", O_RDWR | O_NOCTTY);
for (int i=0; i<sizeof(buffer)/sizeof(uint8_t); i++) {
buffer[i] = '0'+i;
}

int stime = atoi(argv[1]);
if (fd_ > 0) {
for (int j=0; j<2; j++) {
int ret = ::write(fd_, buffer, 16*sizeof(uint8_t));
printf("%d\n", j);
if (ret < 0) {
printf("write fail:%d", ret);
}
usleep(stime*1000);
}
printf("try close\n");
::close(fd_);
printf("closed\n");
}

return 0;
}
```

The topic [position_setpoint_triplet](https://github.com/PX4/Firmware/blob/master/msg/position_setpoint_triplet.msg) refers to the type [position_setpoint](https://github.com/PX4/Firmware/blob/master/msg/position_setpoint.msg) defined in another msg file. This reference is, for example:
```
px4/position_setpoint previous
```

If the topic position_setpoint_triplet is added to the microRTPS bridge, with 
`set(config_rtps_send_topics
   position_setpoint_triplet
   )` in src/modules/micrortps_bridge/CMakeLists.txt
then the following IDL is generated:
```
struct position_setpoint_triplet_
{
	position_setpoint previous;
	position_setpoint current;
	position_setpoint next;

}; // struct position_setpoint_triplet_
```
Then, generate_microRTPS_bridge.py fails with error:
build/posix_sitl_rtps/src/modules/micrortps_bridge/micrortps_client/micrortps_agent/idl/position_setpoint_triplet_.idl:3:1: error: 'position_setpoint' was not defined previously

The topic telemetry_status has a field named `fixed` [https://github.com/PX4/Firmware/blob/master/msg/telemetry_status.msg#L14]()
If this topic is added to the microRTPS bridge, with 
`set(config_rtps_send_topics
   telemetry_status
   )` in src/modules/micrortps_bridge/CMakeLists.txt
then the following IDL is generated:
```
struct telemetry_status_
{
	unsigned long long heartbeat_time;
	unsigned long long telem_time;
	unsigned short rxerrors;
	unsigned short fixed;
	octet type;
	octet rssi;
	octet remote_rssi;
	octet noise;
	octet remote_noise;
	octet txbuf;
	octet system_id;
	octet component_id;

}; // struct telemetry_status_
```
Then, generate_microRTPS_bridge.py fails with error: no viable alternative at input 'fixed'

Apparently, `fixed` is a keyword in the IDL of fastrtpsgen

